.TH frontmatter 1 "May 2026" "frontmatter"
.SH NAME
frontmatter \- print YAML front-matter from files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B frontmatter
.RI [ options ]
.RI < file|dir ...>
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B frontmatter
reads one or more files and prints the YAML front-matter block
\(em the content between the opening and closing
.B \-\-\-
delimiters at the start of the file. When a directory is given it is
searched recursively for files whose first line is
.BR \-\-\- .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.I file
Print the front-matter block from the given file, or warn if none
is found.
.TP
.I directory
Search recursively for files with front-matter blocks. Each match
is printed with a
.B ==> file ==>
header.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns zero when front-matter is found. Returns non-zero when no
front-matter exists in the input, or when an error occurs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B frontmatter post.md
Print front-matter from a single file.
.TP
.B frontmatter src/
Recursively print front-matter from all files under
.IR src/ .
